What is servers composed of?

Compute - CPU
Memory - RAM
Storage - Data
Database - store a data in structured way
Network - Routers, Switches, DNS servers


What is network?
network is a bunch of cables, routers, and servers

What is Router?
router is a network device that will forward the data packets between computer in the networks. They know where to send your packets on the internet.

What is switch?
Takes a pocket and send in to correct server/client on your network.


*** Problems with tradtional IT approach ***
>Pay rent for the data servers
>Pay for Power supply, cooling, maintenance
>Adding and replacing hardware taking much time
>Scalling is limited
>Hire 24/7 team to monitor the infrastructure
>How to deal with disasters?(earchquick, fire, power shutdown...)







